               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; the first line (or the first word) of the ʿarke-hymns after commemorative notes; five groups of red lines alternating with black lines on the incipit page of the months Mäggabit, Miyazya; four groups of red lines alternating with black lines on the incipit page of the months Gǝnbot, Säne, Ḥamle; three groups of red lines alternating with black lines on the incipit page of the month Näḥase; the name of the original donor in the supplication formulas (blotted out); two initial lines of the beginning of commemorative notices for each day; one initial line of each commemorative notice; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numbers; ዘአቅረብኩ and ዘጸሐፎ in the concluding prayers.</rubric>
