                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 162r: Beginning of a record concerning a litigation about land division between the community and &#704;ato G&#228;bri&#7717;ann&#601;s. </span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 162r: </span><span style="font-size: large;">&#4840;&#4635;&#4613;&#4704;&#4653;&#4755;&#4966; &#4843;&#4726;&#4961; &#4872;&#4709;&#4650;&#4624;&#4757;&#4661;&#4966; &#4773;&#4653;&#4677;&#4966;</span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Written in Amharic; robably the same as in Additio 3 of Ms. BGY-001 (fols. 137vс-138ra)</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Internal number of the ecclesiastic library has been crudely written on fol. 1r: ስን No 3-1 24-8-93.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-signs in the shape of two perpendicular lines with loops at the ends of each line, indicating the place where the passages rewritten in the upper margins belong: fols. 4r, 4v, 5r, 5v, 6v.&#xD;
- A sign in the shape of cross (possibly tämälläs-sign, but no omitted text passages are indicated in the margin): e.g., fols. 5vc (between columns b and c, and above column c), 66r (betwen columns b and c), 67r (inner margin), 97v (between columns a and b), 98v, 99r, 99v etc. &#xD;
- Scribbles: fols. 16r, 18r, 119v, upper margin; fols. 142va, bottom margin.&#xD;
- Lacunae: fol. 45rc.&#xD;
- Space for rubricated names is left unfilled in the supplication formulas starting from fol. 101.&#xD;
- Omitted words and passages written interlineally, in the main hand: fol. 70ra, 128rb.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures, in a secondary hand: fols. 72rb, 79vb, 79vc, 85rc, 88ra etc.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with triple thin black lines: fols. 78va, 102rb&#xD;
- The damaged passages are rewritten in a secondary hand, in the upper margin (fols. 2v, 3r, 3v, 4r, 4v, 5r, 5v, 6r, 6v, 7r, 8v, 9r, 9v, 10r, 11r, 13r, 14v, 15r, 16v).&#xD;
- Lost passages are rewritten in a secondary hand: fols. 71v, 162ra.</item>
